Refund API
Last updated December 23rd, 2025

Overview
The Hubtel Refund API allows you to refund monies to customers based on a previous order made. This document focuses on both:

Card transactions Refund.
Mobile money transactions Refund.
bulb-icon
Note
You can only refund transactions within the last 45 days using this API. For older transactions, please send an email to business@hubtel.com.


Getting Started

Business IP Whitelisting
You must share your public IP address with your Retail System Engineer for whitelisting.

bulb-icon
Note
All API Endpoints are live and only requests from whitelisted IP(s) can reach the endpoints shared in this reference.


API Reference
This endpoint can be used to refund a successful mobile money or card transaction on your account. To initiate a request, send an HTTP POST request to the below URL with the required parameters. Passing your Hubtel POS Sales ID for Refund requests in the endpoint is also mandatory. Find your POS Sales ID here.

API Endpoint	https://refund-api.hubtel.com/refund/{Hubtel_POS_Sales_ID}/order/{orderId}
Request Type	POST
Content Type	JSON

REQUEST PARAMETERS
Parameter	Type	Requirement	Description
Hubtel_POS_Sales_ID	Number	Mandatory	The merchant's Hubtel POS Sales ID. Find yours here.
OrderID	String	Mandatory	This is the OrderID from Hubtel for the payment which was processed. Eg. b230733cd56b4a0fad820e39f66bc27c
CallbackURL	String	Mandatory	The callback URL to receive the final notification on the status of the payment

SAMPLE REQUEST
HTTP

copy
Copy
  POST /refund/11684/order/79213a0568c44c13a8a04ba056d681 HTTP /1.1
  Host: refund-api.hubtel.com
  Accept: application/json
  Content-Type: application/json
  Authorization: Basic endjeOBiZa250fT3=
  Cache-Control: no-cache
  {
      "callbackUrl":"https://webhook.site/b503d1a9-e726-f315254a6ede"
  }

RESPONSE PARAMETERS
Parameter	Type	Description
ResponseCode	String	The unique response code on the status of the request
Message	String	The status of the request
Data	Object	An object parameter that gives the details of the transaction whose status is being checked. ie. the order.
OrderId	String	This isthe OrderId from Hubtel for the payment which was processed.

SAMPLE RESPONSE
200 OK

copy
Copy
  {
    "message": "Transaction pending. Expect callback request for final state.",
    "responseCode": "0001",
    "data": {
        "orderId": "b230733cd56b4a0fad820e39f66bc27c"
    }
  }

